<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-595] Installing and deploying source.jars with maven</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-595</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi Mahouts,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was missing source jars for mahout in my maven repository, so I&apos;m adding a patch to this issue, which does the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adds an &amp;lt;execution&amp;gt; to maven-source-plugin&apos;s configuration in /project/build/pluginManagement in the main pom.xml&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adds maven-source-plugin to core/pom.xml, examples/pom.xml, math/pom.xml and utils/pom.xml, without any further configuration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;for each mvn install or mvn deploy this will add an $&lt;/p&gt;
{artifactId}
&lt;p&gt;-{$version}-sources.jar to the repository.&lt;br/&gt;
So Eclipse and other IDEs will be able to use those source jars to make &quot;source-code-hopping&quot; possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The given patch was created using revision 1063288.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kind Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Manuel Me&#223;ner&lt;/p&gt;</description>
